{"title": "Magic Mountain (Volume One)", "description": "Thomas Mann\u2019s epic novel depicts a decaying, corrupted European society on the eve of the First World War. Set in a luxurious sanatorium high up in the Swiss mountains, we follow the destinies of a variety of exotic characters \u2013 members of a bourgeois elite drawn from all parts of Europe. Most suffer from consumption, dream of a cure - yet are at the same time squeezing as much pleasure and distraction as they can out of a situation ever-shadowed by sickness, pain, and death. Part surreal comedy, part grim tragedy, part allegory, and part novel of ideas, Mann\u2019s novel is regarded by many as one of the key literary texts of the twentieth century.\r\nSummary by Steve Gough", "duration": 58847, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "10558", "name": "Thomas Mann"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/magic_mountain_v1_2305_librivox/magic_mountain1_2305.jpg", "copyright_year": "1927", "genres": ["Culture & Heritage Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Steve Gough"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Steve Gough"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Annise"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Annise"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Forward", "readers": [7084], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/magic_mountain_v1_2305_librivox/magic_mountain1_00_mann_64kb.mp3", "duration": 236}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1: Arrival", "readers": [7084], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/magic_mountain_v1_2305_librivox/magic_mountain1_01_mann_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1269}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 1: Number Thirty Four", "readers": [7084], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/magic_mountain_v1_2305_librivox/magic_mountain1_02_mann_64kb.mp3", "duration": 561}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 1: In the Restaurant", "readers": [7084], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/magic_mountain_v1_2305_librivox/magic_mountain1_03_mann_64kb.mp3", "d